parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration can cause loss of vehicle control, leading to accidents, injuries, and fatalities. It can also lead to damage to property and other vehicles.
symptoms: The vehicle suddenly accelerates on its own
and the brakes may not respond or may be ineffective in stopping the vehicle. The acceleration can be rapid and uncontrollable
making it difficult for the driver to maintain control of the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the subframe can cause the left wheel to collapse or come off while driving, leading to accidents and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: particularly in the same location and type as those found in recalled vehicles.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the subframe can cause the lower A-arm to hang by only one end, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: A loud clunking noise while driving
the lower A-arm hanging by only one end

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration can cause the vehicle to move suddenly and unexpectedly, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates suddenly and unexpectedly
the vehicle surges forward without pressing the accelerator pedal
the vehicle takes off rapidly without warning
the engine roars or revs excessively.
